{%- comment -%}
  Ganguram — Cart delivery progress + service options config (Phase 2.11C).

  Publishes window.GanguramDeliveryProgressConfig (display copy) and loads the
  advisory cart UI (assets/ganguram-delivery-progress.js + .css). The UI reads
  window.GanguramDeliveryRules (getProgressData / getServiceOptions) and paints a
  read-only MOV/free-delivery progress bar + delivery service options into the
  cart panel rendered by snippets/ganguram-delivery-progress.liquid.

  ADVISORY / DISPLAY ONLY: no MOV enforcement, no checkout change, no shipping-charge
  change, no cart mutation, no ShipZip/SBZ/zipLogic/Google/resolver change, no
  settings_data.json. Fail-open (no rules / no selection -> the panel hides).

  Copy uses Liquid-SAFE tokens __AMOUNT__ / __DATE__. A single-brace placeholder
  token must NOT appear inside a Liquid output tag — Shopify's Liquid parser treats
  the inner brace as the start of a tag and fails the import. The JS replaces these
  tokens at runtime (and still accepts the older single-brace form). Per-rule
  customer messages (customer_message_for_cart_value / _delivery_date) are also shown.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
  window.GanguramDeliveryProgressConfig = {
    enabled: true,
    copy: {
      movRemaining: {{ 'Add __AMOUNT__ to reach the minimum order.' | json }},
      freeDeliveryRemaining: {{ 'Add __AMOUNT__ more for free delivery.' | json }},
      freeDeliveryUnlocked: {{ 'You’ve unlocked free delivery!' | json }},
      minimumMet: {{ 'Minimum order reached.' | json }},
      deliveryChargeFrom: {{ 'Delivery from __AMOUNT__' | json }},
      freeDelivery: {{ 'Free delivery' | json }},
      datePickerNote: {{ 'Choose a delivery date' | json }},
      earliestNote: {{ 'earliest __DATE__' | json }},
      standardLabel: {{ 'Standard delivery' | json }},
      fourHourLabel: {{ '4-hour delivery' | json }}
    }
  };
</script>
{{ 'ganguram-delivery-progress.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}
<script src="{{ 'ganguram-delivery-progress.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>
